messages.text: Hello, Ashley King? This is Gale Davenport at the Springvale University library.
I was just checking the records. You have an overdue book.
“The Magical Adventures of Sampson and the Whale.”
I’ll return it right after finals.
I know, but I’m swamped until then.
Is that going to be a problem?
What is it? 10 cents a day?
Well why didn’t you contact me sooner?!
We sent you multiple emails with no response.
Sure enough, there are two from the Springvale University library.
I’ve been so stressed lately, I completely missed them.
Ugh, I’m just seeing them now.
I’ve had so much going on.
If I bring it in tonight, can you waive the fee?
I just lost my job and tuition is due next week.
I could really use a break.
It’s also unfair to the students that have been waiting to read that book.
I stare at my phone in shock.
There are other Sampson fans on campus?!
Not as obscure as you might think.
And the fourth installment came out today.
I’m sure some students wanted to reread the third one beforehand.
Tell whoever is next on the list, I’m sorry.
I’ll be there as soon I can.
I throw my phone on my bed, holding back tears.
This is the last thing I need.
My week has already been epically bad…
And this is just the cherry on top.
My “on and off again” boyfriend just flipped things to permanently off.
And my car is in the shop with a blown transmission.
Not to mention, I have two huge tests coming up.
Discovering the Sampson series was the one bright spot in a terrible semester…
And now even this is getting ruined.
With the book in hand, my eyes narrow on the front desk.
A stocky guy sits there, lazily scrolling on the computer.
He certainly doesn’t look like a librarian.
Not a cardigan sweater in sight.
As if he senses my appraisal, his eyes come up.
And then he eyes the book under my arm with a tight expression.
Just as I reach the desk, my phone rings.
My eyes fill with tears again.
There’s just something about getting a call from your mom after a really, really bad week.
I walk away from the desk and hide in an aisle.
I feel a tear course down my cheek.
Jake dumped me for good a few days ago.
Apparently, he doesn’t want to be tied down anymore.
And on the way back from his house…
It’s going to cost a fortune to fix.
That made me late to work, so I got fired.
Oh, and my English teacher hates me.
Even if I study, I don’t think I’ll get a good grade on this final.
I let my mom’s comforting words soothe me.
But I’m feeling a bit more composed.
I wipe my face, clear my throat…
And stride to the front desk with more confidence than I feel.
A few seconds later, he comes out from one of the aisles.
I place the book on the desk.
I’m here to return this book and pay my late fee.
He nods, slowly reaching out to take it.
But then he just stands there for a few seconds, unmoving.
I’m about to say something, when he speaks first.
You said to tell whoever was next on the list you were sorry.
You know, for not returning the book.
He shrugs, giving me a small smile.
Err…yeah. I’ve been following the series since the beginning.
Been hooked since he stole aboard that pirate ship.
I’ve never met anyone else who reads the series.
Let alone someone who looks like him.
I lean toward the desk, unable to help myself.
Do you think Maria is lying?
What do you think is going on there?
Don’t even get me started on the Doctor!
For the next half hour, my troubles fade to the background.
I get lost in conversation with Gale about my favorite series.
I can’t remember the last time I smiled so much.
Finally, there’s a pause in conversation.
It’s been really nice to talk to another fan.
He hands me back my card.
He runs a nervous hand through his thick hair.
Overheard you, when you were on the phone before.
Sounds like you’re…overdue…for some good luck.
I don’t know what to say.
I notice his cheeks are red.
He reaches down and then slides something across the counter.
The next installment in the series.
The book that just came out!
I want to read the third one again anyway.
I just stop myself from hugging him.
I promise I’ll return this one on time!
No. I mean, when we’re both done…
He gives me a shy smile.
Let’s meet over dinner to discuss it?
A cute, thoughtful guy who reads Sampson!
My stomach nearly bursts with excitement.
